subsection.def:
area
                    (面積), in relation to a local vessel, means
                the product of the length overall and the extreme breadth of the vessel;

paragraph.content:
in the case where the vessel is a ferry vessel that is a dynamically
                    supported craft, $3 per unit of the chargeable net tonnage of the
                    vessel;

in the case where the vessel is a ferry vessel that is not a dynamically
                    supported craft, $1.5 per unit of the chargeable net tonnage of the
                    vessel;

in the case of a permission for the vessel to be berthed, moored or anchored at
                any place in the waters of Hong Kong for a period of 12 months, the fee specified in
                column 3 of that Part opposite the type of vessel;

subparagraph.content:
for each day within the permission period that does not fall within a
                    monthly period referred to in subparagraph (i), an amount equal to 1/365 of the
                    fee specified in column 3 of that Part opposite the type of vessel;

the monthly period beginning on the day immediately following the last
                        day of the yearly period or the last yearly period, as the case may be,
                        referred to in subparagraph (i);

schedule.heading:
Fees Prescribed
      for Purposes of Merchant Shipping (Local Vessels) (Certification and Licensing)
      Regulation
